{
  "text": "The combination of spatial and temporal operators is even more challenging [CITATION_1] , and few works exist with a practical perspective. In [CITATION_2] , some of the authors proposed an extension of STL with a somewhere spatial modality, which can be arbitrarily nested with temporal operators, proposing a monitoring algorithm for both the boolean and the quantitative semantics. An extension of SLCS with temporal aspects can be found in [CITATION_3] where the logic has been applied in the context of smart public transportation. In [CITATION_4] , instead, the authors merge the spatial logic of [CITATION_5] within linear temporal logic, by considering atomic spatial properties. They also provide a qualitative and quantitative semantics, and apply it to smart grids and to the formation of patterns in a reaction diffusion model. Contributions. In this work, we present an extension of the Signal Spatio-Temporal Logic (SSTL), that combines the works in [CITATION_6] and [CITATION_7] . We extend SSTL with the topological spatial surround operator, inspired by the spatial until modality defined in [CITATION_8] .",
